Taiwan Stocks Movers: E Ink Holdings, Pixart Imaging, HTC Corp.

-- B y   W e i y i   L i m
-- 
2011-07-08T06:12:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-08/hua-nan-financial-mega-financial-phison-taiwan-stocks-preview.html
Shares of the following companies had
unusual moves in  Taiwan  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 10:35 a.m. in Taipei  The Taiex Index fell 23.87, or 0.3 percent, to 8,749.55.
The gauge has gained 0.1 percent this week, a second consecutive
advance.  E Ink Holdings Inc. (8069)  (8069 TT), the supplier of Amazon.com
Inc.’s Kindle, advanced 1.2 percent to NT$50.70. June sales
surged 73 percent to NT$1.84 billion ($64 million) from a year
earlier, according to a statement filed to Taiwan’s exchange.  Pixart Imaging Inc. (3227)  (3227 TT) lost 2.4 percent to NT$102.
The image sensor maker said June sales fell 36 percent to NT$255
million from a year earlier.  HTC Corp. (2498)  (2498 TT) dropped 4.9 percent to NT$970, the
lowest close since June 30. Mosaid Technologies Inc. sued Sony
Ericsson Mobile Communications (USA) and a HTC unit, alleging
the infringement of three U.S. patents for portable telephone
location-technology. HTC Chief Financial Officer Winston Yung
declined to comment.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Darren Boey at 
 dboey@bloomberg.net . 